COMPTROLLER AA UMAR took over from DC E OCHIBA as the substantive Customs Area Controller (CAC) of Nigeria Customs Service, Western Marine Command (WMC). COMPTR UMAR during his brief handing and taking over at the WMC Headquarters Ibafon-Apapa, Lagos, the outgoing Ag. CAC welcomed and congratulated the substantive Area Controller for his posting. He appreciated the Officers/Men for their unwavering support and cooperation throughout his tenure and urged them to accord maximum support and cooperation to the new Area Controller. In his remark, Comptroller AA UMAR urged the Officers/Men to rededicate themselves to their statutory responsibilities. He charged them to be disciplined and work according to the codes, procedures, departmental instructions and laws as enshrine in the Customs and Excise Management Act Cap C45 2004 as amended. According to the statement sent to the AmehNews and endorsed by ASCI ISAH SULAIMAN CUSTOMS PUBLIC RELATIONS OFFICER WESTERN MARINE COMMAND saying Comptroller AAUMAR was among the Comptrollers who were recently redeployed on the 8 February 2022 by the Comptroller General of Customs, Col. Hameed Ibrahim Ali (Rtd). He further disclosed that the Until his appointment, Comptroller AA UMAR fsi was the Comptroller Discipline at the Customs Headquarters, Abuja.